oyers highly value.', 78, 6, '["6 years HVAC/R experience","Commercial refrigeration systems","RTU maintenance","Split system service","Emergency repair response","Multiple refrigerant types (R-404A, R-448A, R-290)","Installation experience","Retail/restaurant sector knowledge"]', 'Good experience length with consistent employment history. Strong commercial refrigeration background with emergency service experience. However, experience is narrow - lacks residential, heating systems, and new construction exposure.', 70, NULL, '["Add education section","Include specific achievements/metrics","Expand skills section","Add safety record","Include customer service examples","Mention tools/equipment proficiency"]', 'Professional but basic presentation. Resume is well-organized but lacks depth and specific achievements that would make the candidate stand out from other technicians.', '["6 years of consistent HVAC/R experience","EPA 608 Universal certification","Commercial refrigeration expertise","Emergency service experience","Modern refrigerant knowledge including R-290","Diverse client base (retail/restaurants)"]', '["No heating systems experience mentioned","Missing NATE certification","No residential experience","Limited HVAC controls knowledge","No educational background provided","Lacks customer service emphasis"]', '["Pursue NATE certification immediately to increase marketability","Gain experience with heating systems (gas furnaces, heat pumps) through training or job shadowing","Add metrics to experience (response times, customer satisfaction, projects completed)","Include any educational background or trade school completion","Expand skills section to include tools, software, and equipment familiarity"]', 'YES', '2025-10-04 21:03:02', '2025-10-04 21:03:02') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO "analyses" ("id", "candidate_id", "overall_score", "score_out_of_10", "summary", "technical_skills_score", "technical_skills_found", "technical_skills_missing", "technical_skills_feedback", "certifications_score", "certifications_found", "certifications_recommended", "certifications_feedback", "experience_score", "years_of_experience", "relevant_experience", "experience_feedback", "presentation_score", "presentation_strengths", "presentation_improvements", "presentation_feedback", "strengths", "weaknesses", "recommendations", "hiring_recommendation", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES (4, 4, 72, 7, 'Anthony is a solid mid-level commercial HVAC technician with good hands-on experience in RTUs, controls, and service work. While he demonstrates strong commercial experience and relevant certifications, there are gaps in heating systems knowledge and missing key industry certifications that limit his advancement potential.', 75, '["Rooftop unit service (5-20 tons)","VAV systems","Split systems and mini-splits","DDC & BAS controls","Refrigeration piping","Control wiring","Leak detection","Preventive maintenance","Component replacement (TXV, compressor, motor)","Digital thermostat programming","Economizers","Zone sensors"]', '["Heating systems (gas/electric/oil)","Load calculations","Blueprint reading","Ventilation systems","Energy efficiency optimization","Advanced refrigeration cycles","Safety protocols documentation","Customer service skills"]', 'Strong commercial cooling and controls background, but lacks documented heating systems experience and fundamental HVAC theory knowledge. Controls experience with Siemens BAS is valuable and sets him apart from basic technicians.', 65, '["EPA 608 Type II","Siemens HVAC Controls Certification"]', '["EPA 608 Universal","NATE certification","OSHA 10 or 30","Manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, etc.)","Refrigeration Service Engineers Society (RSES) certifications"]', 'Has essential EPA certification but