ndation for the HVAC Dispatcher position. However, they lack direct HVAC dispatch experience, which would be preferred.', 80, '["Clear and organized resume format","Consistent job history","Professionalism in communication"]', '["Lack of specific HVAC Dispatcher job title","Could provide more quantifiable achievements"]', 'The resume is well-presented, with a clear and organized format. The candidate''s communication skills and professionalism are evident. To further improve, they could consider adding a more targeted job title and including more quantifiable achievements from their previous roles.', '["Bilingual","Mechanically & Technically Inclined","Strong Communication Skills","Logistics and Operations Experience","Customer Service Orientation"]', '["Lack of HVAC Industry Knowledge","Limited Dispatch Software Experience","No Direct HVAC Dispatcher Experience"]', '["Obtain HVAC Dispatcher Certification","Gain Experience with Dispatch Software (e.g., ServiceTitan, FieldEdge)","Pursue Continuing Education in HVAC Industry","Highlight Relevant Achievements and Quantifiable Results"]', 'MAYBE', '2025-11-19 23:41:54', '2025-11-19 23:41:54') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO "analyses" ("id", "candidate_id", "overall_score", "score_out_of_10", "summary", "technical_skills_score", "technical_skills_found", "technical_skills_missing", "technical_skills_feedback", "certifications_score", "certifications_found", "certifications_recommended", "certifications_feedback", "experience_score", "years_of_experience", "relevant_experience", "experience_feedback", "presentation_score", "presentation_strengths", "presentation_improvements", "presentation_feedback", "strengths", "weaknesses", "recommendations", "hiring_recommendation", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES (88, 147, 82, 8, 'Anthony is a recent HVAC graduate with 1.5 years of relevant HVAC experience (5 months field installation + 13 months manufacturing testing), placing him in the ''Close to Required'' tier. He has a good quality resume with strong formatting, clear bullets, and professional presentation. His EPA 608 Universal certification, OSHA 10, and Associate''s degree from MATC provide a solid foundation. The score reflects his near-required experience level, excellent resume quality, certifications, no work gaps, stable employment, and local Milwaukee location.', 75, '["HVAC installation (furnaces, condensers, air handlers, RTUs)","Brazing and pipe fitting (copper, PVC, PEX)","Leak detection and pressure testing","Low-voltage wiring and electrical troubleshooting","System diagnostics and performance testing","Refrigeration systems","Blueprint and schematic reading","System start-ups and commissioning","Airflow and refrigerant pressure calibration"]', '["Advanced troubleshooting experience on service calls","Customer interaction and service call management","Preventive maintenance protocols","Ductwork design and fabrication","Heat pump systems experience"]', 'Strong foundational technical skills with hands-on installation and testing experience. The combination of field installation work and manufacturing testing provides good exposure to system performance. However, limited independent service call experience and customer-facing troubleshooting. The technical skills are appropriate for a junior technician or apprentice role but need development in diagnostic service work.', 85, '["EPA 608 Universal Certification","OSHA 10-hour General Industry Safety and Health","Associate''s Degree in HVAC from Milwaukee Area Technical College"]', '["NATE certification (Service Installation or Service Technician)","Manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, Lennox, etc.)","Wisconsin HVAC contractor license (when eligible)","R-410A certification documentation","Advanced electrical/controls training"]', 'Excellent foundational certifications for an entry-level technician. EPA 608 Universal and OSHA 10 are essential and properly obtained. The MATC degree demonstrates comprehensive training. To advance, should pursue NATE certification and manufacturer-specific training to increase marketability and technical credibility.', 78, 1.5, '["HVAC & Construction Technician at Great Lakes Skilled Trades (June 2025 - Present, 5 months): Residential, commercial, and industrial installations including furnaces, condensers, air handlers, RTUs, brazing, leak detection, and system start-ups","HVAC Tester at Desert Aire LLC (January 2024 - January 2025, 13 months): Performance testing, troubleshooting, calibration, and quality control on commercial dehumidifiers and HVAC units"]', 'Has 1.5 years of HVAC experience, placing him at 75% of the required 2 years (Close to Required tier). Experience is well-rounded with both installation and testing/troubleshooting exposure. No work gaps detected - continuous employment from 2019 through present with various roles. Not job hoppy - only 2 HVAC employers with reasonable tenure. The transition from manufacturing testing to field installation shows career progression. Strong work ethic demonstrated by maintaining employment throughout education. Main limitation is the relatively short duration in field service work.', 88, '["Professional LinkedIn-style formatting with clear sections","Strong summary statement that clearly articulates career goals and qualifications","Detailed bullet points with specific technical tasks and accomplishments","No spelling or grammatical errors detected","Excellent organization with certifications, skills, and honors clearly listed","Quantifiable details (dates, locations, specific equipment types)"]', '["Could add metrics or outcomes (e.g., ''completed X installations'' or ''maintained 100% quality rating'')","Consider condensing non-HVAC work history into a single section rather than individual entries","Could highlight any customer satisfaction or performance recognition"]', 'This is a well-crafted, professional resume that clearly communicates qualifications. The formatting is clean and easy to read. The summary section effectively positions the candidate as seeking apprentice/junior roles, which is appropriate for experience level. Technical details in job descriptions demonstrate genuine hands-on work. The inclusion of soft skills (discipline from martial arts) adds personality without being unprofessional.', '["EPA 608 Universal certified with formal HVAC education (Associate''s degree from MATC)","Diverse hands-on experience: both field installation and manufacturing testing/troubleshooting","OSHA 10 certified with strong safety awareness and lockout/tagout protocol experience","Local to Milwaukee area - no relocation concerns","Bilingual (English/Russian) - valuable for diverse customer base","Strong work ethic demonstrated by continuous employment and athletic discipline","Recent graduate (2025) with current, up-to-date training on modern systems"]', '["Only 1.5 years of HVAC experience - falls short of the 2-year requirement by 6 months","Limited independent service call experience - mostly installation and testing support roles","No NATE certification or manufacturer-specific training yet","Relatively new to field work (only 5 months at current position)","May lack experience with customer interaction and service call management","Limited experience with residential service and repair (more installation-focused)"]', '["Pursue NATE Service Technician certification within the next 6-12 months to validate skills and increase marketability","Seek opportunities to shadow experienced service technicians on diagnostic calls to build troubleshooting expertise","Obtain manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, Lennox) through employer training programs","Document any customer interactions or service call completions to build a track record of independent work","Continue building experience in current role for another 6 months to reach the 2-year threshold, then reassess career opportunities","Consider adding metrics to resume (number of installations completed, systems tested, etc.) to quantify contributions"]', 'YES (80-89)', '2025-11-19 23:58:00', '2025-11-19 23:58:00') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO "analyses" ("id", "candidate_id", "overall_score", "score_out_of_10", "summary", "technical_skills_score", "technical_skills_found", "technical_skills_missing", "technical_skills_feedback", "certifications_score", "certifications_found", "certifications_recommended", "certifications_feedback", "experience_score", "years_of_experience", "relevant_experience", "experience_feedback", "presentation_score", "presentation_strengths", "presentation_improvements", "presentation_feedback", "strengths", "weaknesses", "recommendations", "hiring_recommendation", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES (89, 148, 78, 8, 'Brandon has approximately 10+ years of total HVAC experience across multiple roles, significantly exceeding the 2-year requirement. He holds EPA 608 Universal, 410A, and NATE certifications. However, the resume shows job hopping with 6 different HVAC employers in the past 3 years (2022-2025), which is a significant red flag. The resume quality is mid-level with professional formatting but lacks substantive bullet points under most positions. Currently employed with overlapping roles showing strong work ethic, but the frequent job changes substantially impact the overall score.', 75, '["HVAC troubleshooting","Air Conditioning Repair","Boiler Repair","Heating systems","Ventilation systems","Electrical troubleshooting","Gas systems","Plumbing (cross-functional)"]', '["Specific equipment brands/manufacturers","Refrigerant recovery procedures","Ductwork design/installation","Building automation systems","Preventive maintenance protocols","Diagnostic tools proficiency"]', 'Brandon demonstrates broad HVAC technical knowledge across heating, cooling, ventilation, electrical, and gas systems. His background includes supervisory and lead technician roles indicating advanced technical competency. However, the resume lacks specific technical details about equipment serviced, repair procedures performed, or measurable achievements. Adding concrete examples of complex repairs, system types serviced, and technical accomplishments would strengthen this section.', 85, '["EPA 608 Universal","410A certification","NATE certification","PM Tech","Ready to Work (2 instances)"]', '["HVAC Excellence certifications","Manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, Lennox, etc.)","OSHA 10 or 30","State HVAC license (if applicable in Virginia)","Advanced NATE specializations"]', 'Strong certification portfolio with the essential EPA 608 Universal and NATE credentials. The 410A certification is valuable for refrigerant handling. PM Tech and Ready to Work certifications add value. To advance his career and demonstrate commitment to professional development, Brandon should pursue manufacturer-specific certifications and consider additional NATE specializations in areas like heat pumps or air conditioning.', 72, 10.5, '["A-Z HVAC Home Solutions - HVAC Tech (July 2025-Present, 4 months)","JC Heating & Cooling - Manager (June 2024-August 2025, 1 year 3 months)","Roanoke Mechanical - Lead HVAC Technician (December 2023-August 2025, 1 year 9 months)","JC Heating & Air - Service Technician (June 2023-August 2025, 2 years 3 months)","Shenandoah Home Services - HVAC Supervisor (April 2022-July 2023, 1 year 4 months)","Woods Heating & Air - HVAC Technician (April 2015-January 2022, 6 years 10 months)","StarVocity LLC - Small Business Owner (July 2018-Present, 7 years 4 months, appears to be HVAC-related side business)"]', 'Brandon has extensive HVAC experience totaling over 10 years, well exceeding the 2-year requirement. His progression from technician to supervisor to lead roles demonstrates career growth. However, there''s a major concern with job stability: 6 different employers in the past 3 years (2022-2025) indicates significant job hopping. While he shows overlapping employment (positive work ethic), the frequent company changes raise retention concerns. His longest tenure was 6 years 10 months at Woods Heating & Air (2015-2022), but since then he''s averaged less than 1 year per employer. No significant work gaps detected due to overlapping positions.', 65, '["Professional LinkedIn profile included","Clear chronological format","Education section well-organized","Contact information present","Certifications highlighted at top"]', '["Most HVAC positions lack bullet points describing responsibilities and achievements","No quantifiable accomplishments or metrics","Summary section focuses too much on non-HVAC background (medical technology, IT)","Inconsistent formatting in job titles and descriptions","Missing specific technical details about systems serviced","Could benefit from action verbs and concrete examples"]', 'The resume has professional formatting and structure, placing it in the ''mid'' category. However, it significantly lacks substantive content under most HVAC positions. Only a few roles have any descriptive bullets, and most positions are title-only. The summary section is misaligned with HVAC focus, emphasizing medical technology and IT consulting rather than HVAC expertise. To improve, Brandon should add 3-5 bullet points per HVAC role highlighting specific repairs, customer satisfaction metrics, systems serviced, and leadership accomplishments.', '["Extensive HVAC experience (10+ years) far exceeding the 2-year requirement","Strong certification portfolio including EPA 608 Universal and NATE","Leadership experience as supervisor and lead technician demonstrating advancement","Diverse HVAC exposure across residential and commercial systems","Cross-functional skills in electrical, plumbing, and gas systems","Currently employed with overlapping roles showing strong work ethic","Small business ownership demonstrates entrepreneurial drive"]', '["Severe job hopping: 6 different HVAC employers in 3 years (2022-2025) raises major retention concerns","Resume lacks substantive bullet points and specific accomplishments","No quantifiable metrics or achievements listed","Summary section poorly aligned with HVAC career focus","Missing details about specific equipment, brands, or complex repairs performed","Short tenures at recent employers (most under 1.5 years) suggest instability"]', '["Address job stability concerns: Be prepared to explain the frequent job changes in the past 3 years and demonstrate commitment to long-term employment","Add 3-5 substantive bullet points under each HVAC position describing specific responsibilities, repairs, systems serviced, and achievements","Include quantifiable metrics: number of service calls completed, customer satisfaction scores, revenue generated, or efficiency improvements","Rewrite summary section to focus on HVAC expertise rather than medical technology and IT background","Add specific equipment brands and systems expertise (residential vs commercial, specific manufacturers)","Pursue manufacturer-specific certifications to demonstrate ongoing professional development and specialization"]', 'MAYBE (50-79)', '2025-11-19 23:58:45', '2025-11-19 23:58:45') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO "analyses" ("id", "candidate_id", "overall_score", "score_out_of_10", "summary", "technical_skills_score", "technical_skills_found", "technical_skills_missing", "technical_skills_feedback", "certifications_score", "certifications_found", "certifications_recommended", "certifications_feedback", "experience_score", "years_of_experience", "relevant_experience", "experience_feedback", "presentation_score", "presentation_strengths", "presentation_improvements", "presentation_feedback", "strengths", "weaknesses", "recommendations", "hiring_recommendation", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES (90, 149, 92, 9, 'Emad is an exceptional candidate with 8 years of total HVAC experience (4+ years as a Manufacturer Tech Support Service Technician II at Data Aire, plus 4 years of self-employed HVAC work). He holds EPA 608 Universal Certification and 410A certification, has a well-formatted resume with substantive bullets, demonstrates excellent work ethic with overlapping employment (no gaps), and shows strong job stability with long tenures. The resume is professionally presented with detailed technical accomplishments across commercial HVAC systems, data center environments, and diverse equipment types.', 95, '["Commercial HVAC systems","Data Center HVAC","Chilled Water systems","Air, Water, Glycol-Cooled systems with Compressor","Upflow/Downflow Air Distribution","Floor/Ceiling HVAC systems","Indoor/Outdoor Condensers","Economization/Free Cooling","Chillers and AHU","Window AC units","Electrical troubleshooting","Blueprint reading","Duct design","Preventive maintenance","Diagnostics and repair","Building automation","Commercial refrigeration"]', '["Residential split systems experience could be more detailed","Heat pump experience not explicitly mentioned"]', 'Excellent technical breadth with strong emphasis on commercial and data center HVAC systems. Demonstrates advanced skills in chilled water systems, building automation, and complex troubleshooting. The combination of electrical training, blueprint reading, and hands-on repair experience across diverse equipment types is impressive. Experience with manufacturer-specific equipment (Data Aire) adds valuable specialized knowledge.', 85, '["EPA 608 Universal Certification","410A Certification","HVAC Diploma from UEI College"]', '["NATE certification (Service Installation or Commercial Refrigeration)","Manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, Lennox)","HVAC Excellence certifications","State contractor license (if applicable in California)"]', 'Has the essential EPA 608 Universal and 410A certifications required for the role. The HVAC diploma from UEI College provides solid foundational training. To further strengthen credentials, pursuing NATE certification and manufacturer-specific certifications would be beneficial, especially given the extensive commercial experience.', 95, 8, '["Data Aire, Inc. - Manufacturer Tech Support Service Technician II (Sept 2021 - Present): 4 years 2 months - Commercial data center HVAC, diagnostics, repair, preventive maintenance, customer service","Self-employed - HVAC Technician/Contractor (Oct 2017 - Sept 2021): 4 years - Chillers, AHU, window AC units, electrical troubleshooting, installation, repair"]', 'Outstanding experience profile with 8 total years in HVAC (4X the required 2 years). Demonstrates excellent job stability with 4+ years at current employer and 4 years of self-employment prior. No work gaps - employment history shows overlapping transition from self-employment to Data Aire, indicating strong work ethic. Not job hoppy at all - only 2 HVAC employers with long tenures at each. Experience progression from self-employed generalist to specialized manufacturer tech support shows career growth. The 14-year tenure in petroleum industry prior to HVAC demonstrates reliability and commitment.', 88, '["Professional formatting with clear sections","Detailed bullet points with substantive content (2+ bullets per position)","Strong use of action verbs and technical terminology","Well-organized chronological layout","Comprehensive education section with course details"]', '["Minor formatting inconsistency with bullet point styles (mix of â€¢ and )","Could condense the petroleum industry role details since it''s not HVAC-related","Summary section could be more impactful with specific achievements","Some bullets could be more concise"]', 'This is a GOOD quality resume with professional presentation, no significant typos or grammar errors, and substantive content throughout. The formatting is clean and easy to read. Technical details are well-articulated with specific equipment types and systems listed. Minor improvements could include standardizing bullet point formatting and tightening up some of the longer descriptions, but overall this is a strong, professional resume.', '["8 years of total HVAC experience (4X the requirement) with strong commercial and data center specialization","EPA 608 Universal and 410A certifications in place","Excellent job stability - 4+ years at current employer, not job hoppy","Comprehensive technical skills across diverse HVAC systems (chillers, AHU, building automation, economizers)","Strong electrical troubleshooting background with multiple electrical training courses","Customer service experience with manufacturer tech support role","No work gaps - continuous employment with overlapping transition showing work ethic"]', '["Location in Corona, California - distance from job site not specified (could be a concern if over 30 miles)","Could benefit from additional industry certifications like NATE","Limited residential HVAC experience mentioned (primarily commercial focus)","Self-employment period may require verification of experience claims","Previous 14-year career in petroleum industry, though shows reliability, means HVAC career is relatively newer"]', '["Pursue NATE certification to strengthen credentials and demonstrate industry-recognized competency","Consider obtaining manufacturer certifications from major brands (Carrier, Trane, Lennox) to complement Data Aire specialization","Add specific metrics or achievements to summary (e.g., ''maintained 95% first-call resolution rate'' or ''serviced 200+ units annually'')","Clarify location/willingness to travel if job site is beyond 30 miles from Corona, CA","Consider condensing the petroleum industry role to 3-4 bullets to emphasize HVAC experience more prominently"]', 'STRONG_YES (90-100)', '2025-11-19 23:59:27', '2025-11-19 23:59:27') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
