ersal","410A Certification","NATE Certified","PM Tech","Ready to Work (2 certifications listed)"]', '["NATE specialty certifications (Air Conditioning, Heat Pump, Gas Heating)","Manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, Lennox, etc.)","OSHA 10 or 30","State HVAC license (if required in Virginia)"]', 'Strong certification portfolio with the essential EPA 608 Universal and NATE credentials. The 410A certification is valuable for refrigerant handling. The PM Tech and Ready to Work certifications show commitment to professional development. To advance further, pursuing manufacturer certifications and additional NATE specialties would be beneficial.', 75, 10.5, '["A-Z HVAC Home Solutions - HVAC Tech (July 2025-Present, 4 months)","JC Heating & Cooling - Manager (June 2024-August 2025, 1 year 3 months)","Roanoke Mechanical - Lead HVAC Tech (December 2023-August 2025, 1 year 9 months)","JC Heating & Air - Service Tech (June 2023-August 2025, 2 years 3 months)","Shenandoah Home Services - HVAC Supervisor (April 2022-July 2023, 1 year 4 months)","Woods Heating & Air - HVAC Tech (April 2015-January 2022, 6 years 10 months)","Corell Electrical - Electrician (January 2008-July 2013, 5 years 7 months - relevant electrical experience)"]', 'Brandon has extensive HVAC experience totaling 10+ years, well exceeding the 2-year requirement. His progression from technician to supervisor to lead roles shows career growth. However, there''s a concerning pattern of job hopping with 6 different HVAC employers since 2022 (average tenure of 6-8 months each). Multiple overlapping positions indicate strong work ethic but also raise questions about commitment to individual employers. The 6+ year tenure at Woods Heating & Air (2015-2022) shows he can be stable. No significant work gaps detected.', 65, '["Clean, professional LinkedIn-style format","Clear contact information and certifications prominently displayed","Chronological organization is easy to follow","Education section is comprehensive"]', '["Most positions lack bullet points describing responsibilities and achievements","No quantifiable accomplishments or metrics","Summary section is generic and doesn''t highlight HVAC expertise","Some positions only list job title without any description","Could benefit from action verbs and specific technical examples"]', 'The resume has professional formatting and structure, placing it in the ''mid'' category. While visually clean, it lacks substantive content under most job entries. Only the Corell Electrical and Specialized Radiology positions have detailed bullets. HVAC positions need 2-3 bullets each describing key responsibilities, types of systems serviced, and notable achievements. The summary should be rewritten to focus on HVAC expertise rather than medical technology background.', '["Significantly exceeds experience requirement with 10+ years in HVAC","Strong certification portfolio including EPA 608 Universal and NATE","Diverse HVAC experience across residential and commercial sectors","Electrical background (5+ years) provides valuable cross-training","Leadership experience as supervisor and lead technician","Currently employed showing continuous work ethic"]', '["Severe job hopping pattern with 6 employers in 3 years (major red flag)","Resume lacks substantive bullet points describing HVAC work performed","No quantifiable achievements or metrics demonstrating impact","Summary section doesn''t emphasize HVAC expertise","Unclear why candidate left multiple positions after short tenures","Multiple overlapping roles may indicate overcommitment or scheduling conflicts"]', '["Address job stability concerns directly - be prepared to explain frequent job changes in interviews and demonstrate commitment to next employer","Add 2-3 detailed bullet points under each HVAC position describing systems serviced, types of repairs, customer satisfaction, or efficiency improvements","Rewrite summary to focus on HVAC expertise, years of experience, and key technical strengths rather than medical/IT background","Include quantifiable achievements (e.g., ''Maintained 95% first-call resolution rate'' or ''Serviced 200+ residential units annually'')","Consider consolidating overlapping positions or explaining the business model (e.g., contractor working for multiple companies)","Pursue manufacturer-specific certifications to demonstrate ongoing professional development and specialization"]', 'MAYBE (50-79)', '2025-11-20 00:02:45', '2025-11-20 00:02:45') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
