n of electrical training, blueprint reading, and hands-on repair experience across diverse equipment types is impressive. Experience with manufacturer-specific equipment (Data Aire) adds valuable specialized knowledge.', 85, '["EPA 608 Universal Certification","410A Certification","HVAC Diploma from UEI College"]', '["NATE certification (Service Installation or Commercial Refrigeration)","Manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, Lennox)","HVAC Excellence certifications","State contractor license (if applicable in California)"]', 'Has the essential EPA 608 Universal and 410A certifications required for the role. The HVAC diploma from UEI College provides solid foundational training. To further strengthen credentials, pursuing NATE certification and manufacturer-specific certifications would be beneficial, especially given the extensive commercial experience.', 95, 8, '["Data Aire, Inc. - Manufacturer Tech Support Service Technician II (Sept 2021 - Present): 4 years 2 months - Commercial data center HVAC, diagnostics, repair, preventive maintenance, customer service","Self-employed - HVAC Technician/Contractor (Oct 2017 - Sept 2021): 4 years - Chillers, AHU, window AC units, electrical troubleshooting, installation, repair"]', 'Outstanding experience profile with 8 total years in HVAC (4X the required 2 years). Demonstrates excellent job stability with 4+ years at current employer and 4 years of self-employment prior. No work gaps - employment history shows overlapping transition from self-employment to Data Aire, indicating strong work ethic. Not job hoppy at all - only 2 HVAC employers with long tenures at each. Experience progression from self-employed generalist to specialized manufacturer tech support shows career growth. The 14-year tenure in petroleum industry prior to HVAC demonstrates reliability and commitment.', 88, '["Professional formatting with clear sections","Detailed bullet points with substantive content (2+ bullets per position)","Strong use of action verbs and technical terminology","Well-organized chronological layout","Comprehensive education section with course details"]', '["Minor formatting inconsistency with bullet point styles (mix of â€¢ and )","Could condense the petroleum industry role details since it''s not HVAC-related","Summary section could be more impactful with specific achievements","Some bullets could be more concise"]', 'This is a GOOD quality resume with professional presentation, no significant typos or grammar errors, and substantive content throughout. The formatting is clean and easy to read. Technical details are well-articulated with specific equipment types and systems listed. Minor improvements could include standardizing bullet point formatting and tightening up some of the longer descriptions, but overall this is a strong, professional resume.', '["8 years of total HVAC experience (4X the requirement) with strong commercial and data center specialization","EPA 608 Universal and 410A certifications in place","Excellent job stability - 4+ years at current employer, not job hoppy","Comprehensive technical skills across diverse HVAC systems (chillers, AHU, building automation, economizers)","Strong electrical troubleshooting background with multiple electrical training courses","Customer service experience with manufacturer tech support role","No work gaps - continuous employment with overlapping transition showing work ethic"]', '["Location in Corona, California - distance from job site not specified (could be a concern if over 30 miles)","Could benefit from additional industry certifications like NATE","Limited residential HVAC experience mentioned (primarily commercial focus)","Self-employment period may require verification of experience claims","Previous 14-year career in petroleum industry, though shows reliability, means HVAC career is relatively newer"]', '["Pursue NATE certification to strengthen credentials and demonstrate industry-recognized competency","Consider obtaining manufacturer certifications from major brands (Carrier, Trane, Lennox) to complement Data Aire specialization","Add specific metrics or achievements to summary (e.g., ''maintained 95% first-call resolution rate'' or ''serviced 200+ units annually'')","Clarify location/willingness to travel if job site is beyond 30 miles from Corona, CA","Consider condensing the petroleum industry role to 3-4 bullets to emphasize HVAC experience more prominently"]', 'STRONG_YES (90-100)', '2025-11-20 00:03:27', '2025-11-20 00:03:27') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
