ection is slightly lengthy - could be more concise","Could add specific metrics or achievements (number of service calls, customer satisfaction scores)"]', 'This is a well-crafted, professional resume with strong presentation quality. The formatting is clean and easy to read, with no significant typos or grammatical errors. The substantive bullet points effectively communicate responsibilities and skills. Minor improvements would include tightening the summary and adding quantifiable achievements.', '["Exceeds experience requirement with 3.5 years total HVAC experience","Strong educational foundation with Associate''s degree in HVAC/R and multiple certifications","EPA 608 and HVAC Excellence certified - demonstrates commitment to professional standards","Currently employed with stable work history and no gaps in HVAC career","Well-rounded experience covering both maintenance/service and installation work","Excellent work ethic demonstrated by maintaining multiple jobs while completing education","Strong customer service background and communication skills"]', '["Location not specified on resume - distance from job site unknown","Limited mention of specific HVAC equipment brands or manufacturers worked with","No NATE certification yet (though has other strong certifications)","Could provide more specific examples of complex repairs or troubleshooting scenarios","Relatively early in career - may lack experience with some advanced commercial systems"]', '["Pursue NATE certification to complement existing EPA 608 and HVAC Excellence credentials","Add specific metrics to resume (e.g., ''Completed 15-20 service calls per week with 95% first-call resolution rate'')","Highlight specific equipment brands and systems worked on (residential vs. commercial split)","Consider condensing or removing non-HVAC jobs from 2017-2019 to focus resume on HVAC career","Add any manufacturer-specific training or certifications completed through current employer"]', 'STRONG_YES (90-100)', '2025-11-20 00:03:58', '2025-11-20 00:03:58') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO "analyses" ("id", "candidate_id", "overall_score", "score_out_of_10", "summary", "technical_skills_score", "technical_skills_found", "technical_skills_missing", "technical_skills_feedback", "certifications_score", "certifications_found", "certifications_recommended", "certifications_feedback", "experience_score", "years_of_experience", "relevant_experience", "experience_feedback", "presentation_score", "presentation_strengths", "presentation_improvements", "presentation_feedback", "strengths", "weaknesses", "recommendations", "hiring_recommendation", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES (99, 158, 92, 9, 'Jared is an exceptional candidate with 15+ years of comprehensive HVAC experience, significantly exceeding the 2-year requirement. His resume demonstrates extensive expertise across residential, commercial, and light industrial systems including chillers, boilers, refrigeration, and plumbing. Despite a work gap from 2017-2020, his stellar track record of being a top performer across multiple companies, combined with relevant certifications (EPA 608, Heat Exchanger Expert) and a well-formatted resume, places him firmly in the top tier.', 95, '["Industrial Chillers","Industrial Boilers","HVAC Systems","Refrigeration","Solar","IAQ (Indoor Air Quality)","Water Purification/Filtration/Treatment","Pumps","Plumbing","Water Softeners","Electrical (Certified Electrician)","Diagnostic & Troubleshooting","Preventive Maintenance","System Installation","Food Equipment (Broilers, Walk-in Freezers, Ice Machines)"]', '["Building Automation Systems (BAS/BMS)","VRF/VRV Systems"]', 'Exceptional breadth and depth of technical skills spanning residential, commercial, and light industrial applications. The combination of HVAC, electrical, plumbing, and water treatment expertise makes this candidate highly versatile. Experience with specialized equipment like industrial chillers and boilers is particularly valuable.', 85, '["EPA 608 Universal","Heat Exchanger Expert","Food and Safety","Certified Electrician","Water Treatment & Purification Certified","Build a Tech Lennox","Solar World Certificate"]', '["NATE Certification (Service Installation or Senior Technician)","Manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, York)","OSHA 10 or 30"]', 'Strong certification portfolio with EPA 608 Universal and specialized credentials in heat exchangers and water treatment. The electrical certification adds significant value. Adding NATE certification would further strengthen credentials and demonstrate commitment to industry standards.', 95, 15.75, '["Nate''s Plumbing & HVAC - Senior HVAC/Chiller Service Technician (April 2025-Present, 7 months)","Wighton''s Plumbing, Heating, & Air Conditioning - Senior HVAC Service Technician (Oct 2023-March 2025, 1.5 years)","California Aeronautical University - Facilities Specialist (March 2020-Aug 2022, 2.5 years)","All-Air Inc - Sr. Service Tech (Jan 2010-May 2017, 7.4 years)","Bell Brothers Plumbing, Heating and Air Conditioning - Service Technician (June 2007-Jan 2010, 2.7 years)","Starbucks - Service Facilities Technician (Feb 2005-Jan 2007, 2 years)"]', 'Outstanding experience level with nearly 16 years in HVAC service, far exceeding the 2-year requirement. Career progression from technician to senior technician demonstrates growth and expertise. There is a notable 2.75-year gap between May 2017 and March 2020, but this is offset by the extensive overall experience and consistent top performance. Recent job stability shows commitment with 1.5 years at Wighton''s before moving to current role. The consistent pattern of being ranked #1 technician across multiple companies is exceptional.', 88, '["Professional LinkedIn-style format with clear sections","Strong summary statement highlighting key qualifications","Quantifiable achievements (AirTime 500 awards, #1 rankings)","Clear job titles and date ranges","Comprehensive skills listing in header"]', '["Some job descriptions lack detailed bullet points (Nate''s Plumbing has no bullets)","Minor inconsistency in location formatting (some jobs have detailed locations, others don''t)","Could benefit from more quantifiable metrics (number of service calls, customer satisfaction scores)","The tagline ''Just over here fixing what your last tech couldn''t'' is memorable but may come across as unprofessional to some employers"]', 'Well-organized and professional resume with good use of formatting and clear presentation. The awards and achievements section adds significant credibility. While most positions have adequate descriptions, adding more specific accomplishments and metrics to recent roles would strengthen the presentation further.', '["Exceptional 15+ years of hands-on HVAC service experience, far exceeding requirements","Proven track record as top performer - consistently ranked #1 technician across multiple companies with AirTime 500 awards","Comprehensive technical expertise spanning residential, commercial, and light industrial systems including specialized equipment (chillers, boilers)","Multiple relevant certifications including EPA 608 Universal and certified electrician credentials","Strong customer service orientation with demonstrated success in maintenance agreements and lead generation","Leadership experience as former area/regional manager shows advancement potential"]', '["Work gap of approximately 2.75 years between May 2017 and March 2020 (though mitigated by overall strong experience)","Recent job change after only 1.5 years at Wighton''s (though current role is only 7 months, so stability pattern unclear)","Missing NATE certification which is increasingly preferred in the industry","Some job descriptions lack detailed accomplishments and metrics","Location not specified - distance from job site unknown which could impact score if over 30 miles"]', '["Obtain NATE certification to complement existing credentials and demonstrate commitment to industry standards","Add more quantifiable metrics to recent job descriptions (e.g., number of service calls completed, customer satisfaction ratings, revenue generated)","Expand on specific accomplishments at current role (Nate''s Plumbing) with detailed bullet points","Consider toning down the tagline to maintain professionalism while still showing confidence","Clarify the work gap period (2017-2020) if there were any relevant activities, training, or part-time work during that time"]', 'STRONG_YES (90-100)', '2025-11-20 00:04:31', '2025-11-20 00:04:31') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
