work.', 88, '["Professional LinkedIn-style formatting with clear sections","Strong summary statement that clearly articulates career goals and qualifications","Detailed bullet points with specific technical tasks and accomplishments","No spelling or grammatical errors detected","Excellent organization with certifications, skills, and honors clearly listed","Quantifiable details (dates, locations, specific equipment types)"]', '["Could add metrics or outcomes (e.g., ''completed X installations'' or ''maintained 100% quality rating'')","Consider condensing non-HVAC work history into a single section rather than individual entries","Could highlight any customer satisfaction or performance recognition"]', 'This is a well-crafted, professional resume that clearly communicates qualifications. The formatting is clean and easy to read. The summary section effectively positions the candidate as seeking apprentice/junior roles, which is appropriate for experience level. Technical details in job descriptions demonstrate genuine hands-on work. The inclusion of soft skills (discipline from martial arts) adds personality without being unprofessional.', '["EPA 608 Universal certified with formal HVAC education (Associate''s degree from MATC)","Diverse hands-on experience: both field installation and manufacturing testing/troubleshooting","OSHA 10 certified with strong safety awareness and lockout/tagout protocol experience","Local to Milwaukee area - no relocation concerns","Bilingual (English/Russian) - valuable for diverse customer base","Strong work ethic demonstrated by continuous employment and athletic discipline","Recent graduate (2025) with current, up-to-date training on modern systems"]', '["Only 1.5 years of HVAC experience - falls short of the 2-year requirement by 6 months","Limited independent service call experience - mostly installation and testing support roles","No NATE certification or manufacturer-specific training yet","Relatively new to field work (only 5 months at current position)","May lack experience with customer interaction and service call management","Limited experience with residential service and repair (more installation-focused)"]', '["Pursue NATE Service Technician certification within the next 6-12 months to validate skills and increase marketability","Seek opportunities to shadow experienced service technicians on diagnostic calls to build troubleshooting expertise","Obtain manufacturer-specific certifications (Carrier, Trane, Lennox) through employer training programs","Document any customer interactions or service call completions to build a track record of independent work","Continue building experience in current role for another 6 months to reach the 2-year threshold, then reassess career opportunities","Consider adding metrics to resume (number of installations completed, systems tested, etc.) to quantify contributions"]', 'YES (80-89)', '2025-11-20 00:20:35', '2025-11-20 00:20:35') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
